==Japanese==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|en|ja|sort=あめりか}} {{term|lang=en|America}}, from {{term|Americus}}, Latinized form of the forename of {{w|Amerigo Vespucci}} (1451-1512), Italian explorer.

===Pronunciation===
* {{ja-pron|アメリカ|acc=0|acc_ref=NHK}}

===Proper noun===
{{ja-pos|ka|proper|hira=あめりか|rom=Amerika}}

# [[America]], [[USA]]

====Usage notes====
Kanji forms include {{l|ja|亜米利加}} and {{l|ja|亜墨利加}}.  These are seldom used.  However, the abbreviation {{l|ja|米|tr=''Bei''}} is used quite frequently.

====Synonyms====
* {{sense|America}} {{l|ja|米国|tr=[[べいこく]], ''[[Beikoku]]''}}
